section#how.section
  .container
    h2 How to use Beetbox?
    h3 Requirements
    ul
      li
        a(href="https://getcomposer.org/download/") Composer
      li
        a(href="https://www.vagrantup.com/") Vagrant
          |  >= 1.8
      li
        a(href="https://www.virtualbox.org/") VirtualBox
    ul
      li
        a(href="https://github.com/cogitatio/vagrant-hostsupdater") Vagrant Hostsupdater
    pre vagrant plugin install vagrant-hostsupdater
    ul
      li
        a(href="https://github.com/oscar-stack/vagrant-auto_network") Vagrant Auto-network
    pre vagrant plugin install vagrant-hostsupdater
    h3 Quickstart
    pre
      | composer require --dev beet/box
      | vagrant up
    p This will automatically generate a Vagrantfile and the .beetbox directory, which will contain a config.yml file used to configure overrides.
    p You can see some examples in&nbsp;
      kbd
        a(href="https://github.com/beetboxvm/beetbox/blob/master/.beetbox/config.yml") config.yml
    h3 Updating
    pre composer update beet/box
    p Version constraints should automatically keep you to the same minor release.&nbsp;
      kbd (0.0.x)
      |  However, you may need to update your configuation when upgrading minor releases.&nbsp;
      kbd (0.x.0)
      |  See the release notes for more information.